Interaction.Comment: Immunoglobulin A (IgA) can bind to the S1 domain of the SARS-CoV-2 spike protein leading to an early burst of IgA that may eliminate the virus in the respiratory mucosa and prevent the development of full adaptive immune response.
Immunolobulin M can bind to the RBD of the S1 domain of the SARS-CoV-2, acting as primary immune response.
The increase of TGFß production induces the IgA isotype switch.
High levels of viral load stimulate TGFß production, which is locally secreted.
TGF-beta signalling pathway enhanced; Observed in SARS-CoV hypothesises to be conserved in SARS-CoV-2
